    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.14-15_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Jonesburg, <del>M</del><add>M</add>issouri
                        January 13, 1959
                    </dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Congrayulations<sic>Congratulations</sic> on the television award that you received last evening! I was surprised and pleased to see <del>t</del><add>y</add>ou on the Missouri Forum Program.</p> 
                
                <p>While I was a patient in Boone County Ho<del>p</del><add>s</add>pital I talked to you on the phone. I am sorry I do not live near enough to come to your office, as there are several questions I would like to ask. Here are some of them: 
                    <lb/>
                    <list>
                        <item>1. Will the examination January 24 cover the whole <del>co</del> course, or only the second half?</item>
                        <item>2. Jed Smith was killed in territory that is now what state? What<del>e</del> date?</item>
                        <item>3. What is the date of the surrender of the last Indians? Were the Sioux the last to be conquered?</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                
                <p>I have very thourghly<sic>thoroughly</sic> enjoyed ever ses<add>s</add>ion of the course. Some time I hope I can meet you. I would like to get a copy of the Easter poem you read during the first half of the class.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Jane Coleman</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P. S.</hi></opener> <p>I just recieved<sic>received</sic> the notice about the exam.</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
